## 2. SDK CORE CONTRACTS

### A. Channel Plugin Entry Point
**File:** `src/plugin-sdk/core.ts`

**Main Entry Helper - `defineChannelPluginEntry()`:**
```typescript
export function defineChannelPluginEntry<TPlugin>({
  id,
  name,
  description,
  plugin,
  configSchema = emptyPluginConfigSchema,
  setRuntime,
  registerCliMetadata,
  registerFull,
}: DefineChannelPluginEntryOptions<TPlugin>): DefinedChannelPluginEntry<TPlugin>
```

**Key Features:**
- Registers channel capability with OpenClaw runtime
- Handles both setup-only and full runtime registration modes
- Returns object with `{ id, name, description, configSchema, register, channelPlugin }`

### B. Chat Channel Plugin Builder - `createChatChannelPlugin()`
**High-level wrapper** for standard chat-style channels (Slack, Discord, etc.)

```typescript
export function createChatChannelPlugin<TResolvedAccount>({
  base: ChatChannelPluginBase,
  security?: ChatChannelSecurityOptions | ChannelSecurityAdapter,
  pairing?: ChatChannelPairingOptions | ChannelPairingAdapter,
  threading?: ChannelThreadingOptions | ChannelThreadingAdapter,
  outbound?: ChatChannelAttachedOutboundOptions | ChannelOutboundAdapter,
}): ChannelPlugin
```

**Composed from:**
- DM security policies (with allowlist support)
- Text-based pairing/approval
- Reply-to threading modes
- Attached send results (channel names auto-filled)

### C. Channel Plugin Base - `createChannelPluginBase()`
**Lower-level builder** for channels that only override optional surfaces

```typescript
export function createChannelPluginBase<TResolvedAccount>(params: {
  id: string;
  meta?: Partial<ChannelMeta>;
  setup: NonNullable<ChannelPlugin['setup']>;
  setupWizard?: ChannelPlugin['setupWizard'];
  capabilities?: ChannelCapabilities;
  agentPrompt?: ChannelAgentPromptAdapter;
  streaming?: ChannelStreamingAdapter;
  reload?: ChannelPlugin['reload'];
  gatewayMethods?: string[];
  configSchema?: ChannelPlugin['configSchema'];
  config?: ChannelPlugin['config'];
  security?: ChannelSecurityAdapter;
  groups?: ChannelGroupAdapter;
}): CreatedChannelPluginBase
```

