# PulseBoard Channel Plugin – Implementation Plan

## Context

OpenClaw supports pluggable messaging channel backends through a well-defined plugin SDK. We are adding a new **fictional** "PulseBoard" channel plugin — a real-time bulletin board platform where users post to named boards (`#board-name`) and exchange direct messages. The goal is a fully-structured, idiomatic extension at `extensions/pulseboard/` that mirrors the IRC and Nostr plugin patterns exactly, without touching any existing files.

Requirements:
- Supports **both direct and group** chat types
- 4000-character text chunk limit
- API token auth (`PULSEBOARD_TOKEN` env var) + workspace URL (`PULSEBOARD_URL`)
- Board targets: `#board-name` (group), user targets: `username` or `@username` (DM)
- Full DM policy support (pairing/open/allowlist/disabled)
- Group policy support (allowlist/open/disabled)
- `pulseboard:` URL scheme prefix stripping in target normalization
- Setup wizard for credentials

**Constraint**: No existing files may be modified. All files are new, under `extensions/pulseboard/`.

---

## Architecture Summary

Follows `extensions/irc/` exactly. Key SDK contracts:
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core` — `defineChannelPluginEntry`, `defineSetupPluginEntry`, `createChatChannelPlugin`, `getChatChannelMeta`, `tryReadSecretFileSync`, `parseOptionalDelimitedEntries`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store` — `createPluginRuntimeStore`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-helpers` — `createAccountListHelpers`, `describeAccountSnapshot`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-id` — `DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID`, `normalizeAccountId`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/account-resolution` — `resolveMergedAccountConfig`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/secret-input` — `normalizeResolvedSecretInputString`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-helpers` — `createScopedChannelConfigAdapter`, `createScopedDmSecurityResolver`, `adaptScopedAccountAccessor`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-config-schema` — `buildChannelConfigSchema`, `DmPolicySchema`, `GroupPolicySchema`, `MarkdownConfigSchema`, `ToolPolicySchema`, `requireOpenAllowFrom`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/channel-policy` — `composeAccountWarningCollectors`, `createAllowlistProviderOpenWarningCollector`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/allow-from` — `formatNormalizedAllowFromEntries`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/directory-runtime` — `createChannelDirectoryAdapter`, `createResolvedDirectoryEntriesLister`
- `openclaw/plugin-sdk/status-helpers` — `createComputedAccountStatusAdapter`, `createDefaultChannelRuntimeState`
