### 11. `extensions/pulseboard/src/normalize.ts`

Pure string normalization utilities — no imports from runtime.

Key exports:
- `isBoardTarget(target: string): boolean` — returns `true` if target starts with `#`
- `normalizePulseBoardMessagingTarget(raw: string): string | undefined` — strips `pulseboard:`, `board:`, `user:`, `@` prefixes; normalizes board targets to have `#`; validates with `looksLikePulseBoardTargetId`
- `looksLikePulseBoardTargetId(raw: string): boolean` — validates with a regex `/^[a-zA-Z0-9_#@.-]+$/u` (no spaces, no special chars)
- `normalizePulseBoardAllowEntry(raw: string): string` — lowercase trim, strip `pulseboard:` or `user:` prefix
- `normalizePulseBoardAllowlist(entries?: Array<string|number>): string[]`
- `buildPulseBoardAllowlistCandidates(message: PulseBoardInboundMessage): string[]` — returns `[senderId.toLowerCase()]`
- `resolvePulseBoardAllowlistMatch(params: { allowFrom: string[]; message: PulseBoardInboundMessage }): { allowed: boolean; source?: string }` — checks wildcard `*` and exact match on sender id

